<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-06-25T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-06-25T09:00:00-05:00" n="160" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d160">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/12454:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-06-25T17:00:00+03:00">June
                                        25, 1941—5 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received June 25—4:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1218. Department’s 840, June 24, 7 p.m. The Soviet Union has not
                                issued a formal proclamation of war against Germany or against
                                Italy. The status of Soviet-German relations was announced in
                                Molotov’s address on June 22,<note n="90" xml:id="d160fn90">See
                                    telegram No. 1197, June 22, from the Ambassador in the Soviet
                                    Union, <ref target="#pg_625">p. 625</ref>.</note> and no
                                reference whatever has been made to Italy.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>